# Cursor Rules

## Project Patterns
1. All code must be written in English
2. Documentation should be comprehensive and up-to-date
3. Testing is mandatory for all new features
4. Error handling must be robust and logged
5. Database operations must be transactional

## User Preferences
1. Portuguese language for communication
2. Clear documentation of changes
3. Regular progress updates
4. Comprehensive testing approach
5. Security-first mindset

## Development Workflow
1. Document changes in Memory Bank
2. Write tests before implementation
3. Review code before committing
4. Update documentation as needed
5. Maintain clear commit messages

## Code Style
1. Follow PEP 8 guidelines
2. Use type hints
3. Document functions and classes
4. Keep functions small and focused
5. Use meaningful variable names

## Testing Approach
1. Unit tests for all components
2. Integration tests for flows
3. End-to-end testing
4. Performance testing
5. Error scenario testing

## Documentation Standards
1. Keep Memory Bank updated
2. Document all changes
3. Maintain clear structure
4. Use diagrams when helpful
5. Include examples

## Security Practices
1. Protect sensitive data
2. Validate all inputs
3. Handle errors securely
4. Log security events
5. Regular security reviews 